Description:
RBH presently operates a fleet of commercial vehicles numbering 151. The current fleet is provided by a vehicle lease provider and are on a 48 month lease.  
The purpose of this tender exercise is to enter into a new contract with an appropriate fleet provider to replace the current fleet on a 48 month lease basis.
The fleet enables RBH to provide the following services:
•	Responsive (Day to Day) repair service: this includes multiple trades including electricians, plumbers, joiners, plasterers and general labourers;
•	Empty Homes service: small teams of mixed trades bringing empty homes up to standard prior to re letting the home;
•	Gas Servicing: a team dedicated to undertaking our annual gas servicing and repairs;
•	Caretaking: this team ensures our neighbourhoods are clean, presentable and safe.  They handle litter and dumped items.  This includes a hit squad dealing with large areas of waste land, fly tipping and garden clearances;
•	Grounds Maintenance. This involves maintaining all green areas of RBH responsibility, including grassed areas, borders, shrubs and trees
•	Health & Safety: this team undertakes statutory health and safety tests on our homes
•	Facilities Management: this team manage and service our office and welfare buildings;
•	Warden servicing: this team provides a 24/7 responsive service to older people and those with restricted mobility throughout the community;
•	Pass it On: this team deliver a furniture recycling services to our tenants, involving the collection and delivery of large and multiple furniture items;
•	Safegard Security: who install and manage fire detection and intruder systems and a comprehensive CCTV system;
